# Trivy ignore list — TRIAGED, TIME-BOXED CVE exceptions only.
#
# The CI image scan (.github/workflows/ci.yml → "Scan … (Trivy)") BLOCKS the GHCR push on any
# FIXABLE HIGH/CRITICAL CVE. This file is the ONLY escape hatch: a specific, understood
# vulnerability that cannot be cleared yet (e.g. a base-image fix hasn't landed upstream) is
# listed here so it doesn't wedge deploys — while every NEW/unknown finding still fails the gate.
#
# Rules:
#   • one CVE id per line, each with a comment: what it is, why it's safe-to-defer, and an EXPIRY date.
#   • re-triage on every base-image re-pin; delete anything that no longer appears in the scan.
#   • never add a blanket wildcard.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-XXXX-YYYYY  # <why deferred> — expires YYYY-MM-DD
#
# (empty = the gate is fully strict; add an id only after you've read the Trivy log and triaged it.)
#
# ── Triaged 2026-07-03 (server image; client image scans clean) ──────────────────────────────
# `npm audit` on our actual dependency tree = 0 vulnerabilities. Every id below lives in a
# DEV-TOOLCHAIN binary that is shipped into the image only because the server runs its TypeScript
# via `tsx` (which bundles esbuild) — none is reachable by an attacker against the running server.
# The proper long-term fix is a COMPILED runtime image (tsc → dist, `npm ci --omit=dev`) that drops
# the whole dev toolchain; until that's done + tested, defer these. Re-check each on the next base
# re-pin — most clear when esbuild/tsx ship a build made with a newer Go, or npm bumps its bundles.
#
# (bare ids only — comments on their own lines above, to avoid any inline-parse ambiguity.)
# EXPIRES 2026-10-03 — re-run the scan on the next base re-pin and delete anything that's gone.
#
# Go stdlib, compiled into esbuild's Go binary. esbuild ships in the image only because the server
# runs its TypeScript via `tsx` (which bundles esbuild); esbuild runs at BOOT to transpile OUR OWN
# trusted source and is NOT a network service — these net/crypto/parser CVEs are unreachable at runtime:
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2025-68121
CVE-2026-25679
CVE-2026-27145
CVE-2026-32280
